From: Kuninori Morimoto <kuninori.morimoto.gx@renesas.com>
Date: Mon, 2 Aug 2021 15:00:27 +0900
Subject: [PATCH] ASoC: soc-topology: cleanup cppcheck warning at soc_tplg_process_headers()
Git-commit: f79e4b2a38eda4e365f765d363f47cf0c2183ab4
Patch-mainline: v5.15-rc1
References: jsc#PED-850

This patch cleanups below cppcheck warning.

sound/soc/soc-topology.c:2576:27: style: The scope of the variable 'hdr' can be reduced. [variableScope]
 struct snd_soc_tplg_hdr *hdr;
                          ^

Signed-off-by: Kuninori Morimoto <kuninori.morimoto.gx@renesas.com>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/87sfzswflw.wl-kuninori.morimoto.gx@renesas.com
Signed-off-by: Mark Brown <broonie@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 sound/soc/soc-topology.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/sound/soc/soc-topology.c b/sound/soc/soc-topology.c
index 0a24d0d409d2..9aa7c9c4768b 100644
--- a/sound/soc/soc-topology.c
+++ b/sound/soc/soc-topology.c
@@ -2572,13 +2572,13 @@ static int soc_tplg_load_header(struct soc_tplg *tplg,
 /* process the topology file headers */
 static int soc_tplg_process_headers(struct soc_tplg *tplg)
 {
-	struct snd_soc_tplg_hdr *hdr;
 	int ret;
 
 	tplg->pass = SOC_TPLG_PASS_START;
 
 	/* process the header types from start to end */
 	while (tplg->pass <= SOC_TPLG_PASS_END) {
+		struct snd_soc_tplg_hdr *hdr;
 
 		tplg->hdr_pos = tplg->fw->data;
 		hdr = (struct snd_soc_tplg_hdr *)tplg->hdr_pos;
